On Tue, 23 Nov 2004, Zach Freshman wrote:

> I'm all set to put in my new alternator. One question though. On my old
> generator, the shaft has a male key, but the new alternator has a female
> key...is this going to be a problem. Do I need to buy a new fan hub,
> what about my pulley??

Hmmm, every generator and alternator I've seen has a half-moon key at each
end of the shaft.  I just took it out of one unit and put it into the
other.  I've a feeling that your "male" key is simply the half-moon key
stuck in the shaft.  Get a punch and give it a few taps and it should come
loose.

George
